# Pantheon-Prime — Missing Organs & Fixes v1.0  
**(No-Junk-DNA Doctrine)**

Pantheon-Prime already contains a *complete genome*: doctrine, invariants, daemons, governance language, and failure awareness.  
What it is intentionally light on is **expression** — the connective tissue that turns a genome into a running organism.

This document records the **missing organs** required to move from *conceptually complete* to *operationally alive*, along with their precise fixes.  
Nothing here replaces or invalidates existing artifacts.  
Under the **No-Junk-DNA rule**, all prior work is treated as **spec, regulatory tissue, immune memory, or fossil lineage**.

---

## 1. Canonical Package Tree (Executable Spine)

**Missing:**  
Imports reference `pantheon.core`, `pantheon.governance`, `pantheon.daemons`, etc., but no unified package tree enforces this structure.

**Fix:**  
Create a canonical Python package:

pantheon/
├── core/
├── governance/
├── daemons/
├── ledger/
├── providers/
└── init.py

Refactor existing stubs and scripts into these modules **without deleting source material**.

**Why it matters:**  
This is the executable spine that allows doctrine to bind to code.

---

## 2. Reproducible Environment & Dependency Lock

**Missing:**  
Environment setup exists conceptually but is not enforced.

**Fix:**  
- Add or correct `pyproject.toml`
- Pin Python version
- Lock dependencies (`uv.lock` / `poetry.lock`)
- Add `Makefile` or `justfile` for common actions

**Why it matters:**  
Reproducibility is a prerequisite for continuity.

---

## 3. Golden-Path Demo (Proof of Life)

**Missing:**  
There is no single, minimal command that boots Pantheon end-to-end.

**Fix:**  
Provide:

```bash
python -m pantheon.demo

This should:
	1.	Instantiate StateVector
	2.	Create a ThoughtObject
	3.	Run ΣC governance
	4.	Route through daemons
	5.	Emit output + ledgered logs

Why it matters:
A single runnable path is the strongest adoption vector.

⸻

4. Provider Adapter Layer (I/O Nervous System)

Missing:
Pantheon speaks as a multi-model control plane, but adapters are implicit.

Fix:
Implement:

pantheon/providers/
├── openai.py
├── anthropic.py
├── local.py
└── base.py

With:
	•	shared interface
	•	retries + circuit breakers
	•	fallback chaining

Why it matters:
This is how Pantheon becomes model-agnostic and future-proof.

⸻

5. Formal Schemas (Contracts Over Vibes)

Missing:
StateVector, ThoughtObject, and ledger entries are conceptually defined but not formally locked.

Fix:
Add versioned JSON schemas:

schemas/
├── state_vector.schema.json
├── thought_object.schema.json
├── ledger_entry.schema.json
└── reason_card.schema.json

Validate at runtime.

Why it matters:
Schemas prevent drift while allowing evolution.

⸻

6. Governance-as-Code (ΣC Made Executable)

Missing:
ΣC is central but not enforced via a policy engine.

Fix:
Implement a governance engine with:
	•	explicit reason codes
	•	allow / deny / degrade ladder
	•	explainable decisions
	•	audit hooks

Why it matters:
Ethics must compile, not merely advise.

⸻

7. Test Harness + CI (Selection Pressure)

Missing:
There is no automated selection pressure enforcing invariants.

Fix:
	•	Add pytest suite asserting:
	•	hashing integrity
	•	redaction rules
	•	ΣC gates
	•	Add GitHub Actions CI

Why it matters:
Systems evolve correctly only under pressure.

⸻

8. Threat Model & Misuse Boundaries

Missing:
Constraints are implied but not explicitly declared.

Fix:
Add THREAT_MODEL.md:
	•	abuse cases
	•	non-goals
	•	“never do” constraints
	•	red-team scenarios

Codify guardrails in governance code.

Why it matters:
If you don’t define limits, critics will define them for you.

⸻

9. Observability & Ledger Spec (Beaver Layer)

Missing:
Logging and ledger concepts exist, but telemetry is not standardized.

Fix:
Define:
	•	structured logs
	•	trace IDs
	•	hashed event ledger
	•	redaction rules
	•	retention tiers

Optional OpenTelemetry hooks.

Why it matters:
Long-lived systems fail silently without observability.

⸻

10. Canon Promotion Workflow (Evolution Without Chaos)

Missing:
No formal rule governs how artifacts become invariants.

Fix:
Create CANON.md describing:
	•	promotion criteria
	•	dual-review requirements
	•	demotion to fossil
	•	changelog discipline

Why it matters:
This is how Pantheon scales without collapsing into myth.

⸻

Final Diagnosis

Pantheon-Prime does not lack ideas.
It lacks expression infrastructure.

The genome is complete.
These organs allow it to live.

Nothing here deletes prior work.
Everything here binds it into a running system.

— Money Bin / No-Junk-DNA v1.0

